      • getSqlCommand

        public String getSqlCommand​(boolean countOnly)
        Get the applicable SQL command up to and including the 'WHERE' keyword (the remainder has been created by the visit* methods). Make sure this SqlFilterExpressionVisitor was subject to an "accept" call before calling this method!
        Parameters:
        countOnly - create a command, which only counts the requested products, but does not return them
        Returns:
        a partial SQL command string

      • visitMethodCall

        public String visitMethodCall​(org.apache.olingo.server.api.uri.queryoption.expression.MethodKind methodCall,
                              List<String> parameters)
                       throws org.apache.olingo.server.api.uri.queryoption.expression.ExpressionVisitException,
                              org.apache.olingo.server.api.ODataApplicationException
        Evaluation of a method call. Currently only the methods "contains", "startswith" and "endswith" are implemented
        Specified by:
        visitMethodCall in interface org.apache.olingo.server.api.uri.queryoption.expression.ExpressionVisitor<String>
        Parameters:
        methodCall - the method to execute
        parameters - the parameters to pass to the method
        Returns:
        application return value of any type
        Throws:
        org.apache.olingo.server.api.uri.queryoption.expression.ExpressionVisitException - in no case (not used)
        org.apache.olingo.server.api.ODataApplicationException - if the parameters are not applicable or insufficient for the requested method, or if an unimplemented method was requested
